To belong is the peace I seek.  It is only found with BOC.  Some listen, nod with respect, and feigned understanding, but the look in their eyes show the shallow social politeness.  Others aren't so kind and merely walk away if I am lucky.  Even now within this week I have found myself avoiding a volatile situation by not saying I was a Vet.<br><br>
We are BOC because we do not have to express what we feel for each other.  There is no burning requirement.  Just being part of the team is enough.  Not unlike the Wolf Pack that Ed has said so much about.  The native Americans understood the binding honor among the pack and their willingness to die for each other.  Respect is a simple gift.<br><br>
Just to be here is enough.<br><br>
YBOC
